  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-06-30",
    "date": "2022-04-01T18:28:11Z",
    "text": "Wildland Firefighter Fair Pay Act\n\nThis bill exempts federal wildland firefighters in the Department of the Interior, the Department of Agriculture (USDA), and the Department of Commerce from certain premium pay limitations for work relating to wildfire emergencies.\n\nThe bill applies retroactively to January 1, 2020.\n\nInterior and USDA must each separately submit a report to specified congressional committees on the resources, policies, personnel or structural changes, and other investments necessary to support an expanded full-time, year-round firefighting workforce."
  },
